Name: Apevia Prestige
Extra Notes/Information: Same platform as Xigmatek Hydra M; reports of dual-sourcing w/ Andyson for US; other models possibly affected.

Name: Silverstone ST85F-GS-V2
Extra Notes/Information: Claims an ICB fan; Aris showed a rifle bearing. OPP set high (~150%;) OOS 3.3V transients. Noisy (>50dBA@750W load). Dual EPS on 18AWG cable.

Name: MSI MAG A850GL PCIE5
Extra Notes/Information: Solid electrical performance; let down by poorly tuned protections; mediocre transient response; and a low quality fan.

Name: Vetroo 50315153244479
Extra Notes/Information: Advertised as ATX 3.1. Platform has poor transient response in 200% ATX 3.1 test; weak 3.3V load regulation; and high-set OCP on minor rails.

Name: SeaSonic Focus GX V4 ATX 3 (2024)
Extra Notes/Information: Black model has white line accents; compared to V3. Stupidly high inrush current; mediocre transient response; minor rails' OCP needs tuning.

Name: Montech CENTURY II
Extra Notes/Information: Good performance and noise profile. High inrush current. OPP and OCP on the minor rails need tuning. Functional; but set high.
